<item>
            <title>[SOLR-8870] AngularJS Query tab breaks through proxy</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8870</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The AngularJS Query tab generates a request URL on this form: &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8983/solr/techproducts%2Fselect?_=1458291250691&amp;amp;indent=on&amp;amp;q=ram&amp;amp;wt=json&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8983/solr/techproducts%2Fselect?_=1458291250691&amp;amp;indent=on&amp;amp;q=ram&amp;amp;wt=json&lt;/a&gt; Notice the urlencoded &lt;tt&gt;%2Fselect&lt;/tt&gt; part.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This works well locally with Jetty, but a customer has httpd as a proxy in front, and we get a 404 error since the web server does not parse &lt;tt&gt;%2F&lt;/tt&gt; as a path separator and thus does not match the proxy rules for select.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12951476">SOLR-8870</key>
