                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15201250" author="janhoy" created="Fri, 18 Mar 2016 09:45:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, the AngularJS code for query panel does not handle qt not prefixed with slash at all (legacy handleSelect=true and qt=foo). It will simply generate a url with core name and qt concatenated together, causing a 404. I&apos;ll attempt to fix that as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15201279" author="janhoy" created="Fri, 18 Mar 2016 10:18:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch which avoids encoding handler part. It also checks whether the handler starts with &quot;/&quot;, and if not, adds handler name as &lt;tt&gt;&amp;amp;qt&lt;/tt&gt; param with &lt;tt&gt;/select&lt;/tt&gt; as hardcoded handler. Tested locally on master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15203431" author="upayavira" created="Sun, 20 Mar 2016 18:47:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good to me (not tried it though)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15217799" author="janhoy" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2016 11:00:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to branch_5_5, branch_5x, branch_6x and master&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
